00:23:11,340 --> 00:23:14,510
Kim Han Yeong has been revealed as the culprit.

315
00:23:14,510 --> 00:23:16,000
What's his motive?

316
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:18,330
It has yet to be revealed through our investigation,

317
00:23:18,330 --> 00:23:21,890
so the culprit is currently being transferred to the law office.

318
00:23:21,890 --> 00:23:24,660
But we've learned quite a shocking truth.

319
00:23:24,660 --> 00:23:30,440
I'm troubled by how to process this information.

320
00:23:30,440 --> 00:23:34,450
In the process of conducting Kim Ham Yeong's background check...

321
00:23:34,450 --> 00:23:39,850
The identity of the person who shot at the Landmine Hero this morning is shocking many.

322
00:23:39,850 --> 00:23:43,960
It has been revealed that Soldier Kim is the brother of the soldier

323
00:23:43,960 --> 00:23:46,710
Landmine Hero Won Gi Chun risked his life to save.

324
00:23:46,710 --> 00:23:50,430
And they've just arrived, as we speak.

325
00:23:50,430 --> 00:23:52,500
What's the reason for your actions?

326
00:23:52,500 --> 00:23:54,220
What was your motive?

327
00:23:54,220 --> 00:23:57,000
How did you sneak the gun out?

328
00:23:59,420 --> 00:24:03,650
Shooting of Battalion Commander Won Gi Chun

329
00:24:03,650 --> 00:24:08,350
Corporal Kim Han Yong was in charge of guns and ammunition at the 4th Division.

330
00:24:26,530 --> 00:24:29,220
He fabricated documents after he completed his inspection.

331
00:24:29,220 --> 00:24:35,210
He stole the model K5 gun and bullets that were used in the crime.

332
00:24:35,210 --> 00:24:37,460
Pass

333
00:24:40,490 --> 00:24:42,290
Unity.

334
00:24:44,050 --> 00:24:47,180
As soon as he left the premises, he went straight to the bookstore, which was the location of the crime.

335
00:24:47,180 --> 00:24:50,630
It seems he prepared for his actions in the bathroom.

336
00:25:03,800 --> 00:25:07,030
He used blank bullets, didn't he?

337
00:25:07,030 --> 00:25:10,940
How did you know? We were just about to give that in our report.

338
00:25:10,940 --> 00:25:15,040
Blank bullets have no deadly projectile, so the rebound is smaller when pulling the trigger.

339
00:25:15,040 --> 00:25:16,540
They sound different too.

340
00:25:16,540 --> 00:25:18,850
If a real bullet goes "bang,"

341
00:25:18,850 --> 00:25:22,090
then a blank sounds like "thunk."

342
00:25:22,090 --> 00:25:25,520
Is that possible to differentiate through CCTV footage?

343
00:25:25,520 --> 00:25:30,500
It's almost as if you were on the scene when it happened.

344
00:25:30,500 --> 00:25:33,380
Shouldn't you know how sharp I am by now?

345
00:25:33,380 --> 00:25:37,060
If it was a blank bullet, it means he had no murderous intent.

346
00:25:37,060 --> 00:25:38,210
Not necessarily.

347
00:25:38,210 --> 00:25:40,490
It's not possible to kill someone with a blank bullet.

348
00:25:40,490 --> 00:25:46,150
What if he had planned to use real bullets but accidentally reloaded using blank ones?

349
00:25:58,170 --> 00:26:02,400
Corporal Kim Han Yong is an ammunition soldier. He can easily tell them apart.

350
00:26:02,400 --> 00:26:05,760
In this case, he stole the gun with the purpose to kill someone though.

351
00:26:05,760 --> 00:26:07,910
This is real life.

352
00:26:07,910 --> 00:26:10,260
Kim Han Yong had real bullets with him at the time of the crime, correct?

353
00:26:10,260 --> 00:26:14,880
Yes. Eight real bullets were found in his pockets.
Evidence Item 2

354
00:26:14,880 --> 00:26:17,700
As expected, a clear intent to kill.

355
00:26:17,700 --> 00:26:23,540
It was a blank shot but he had real bullets on him, so this has to be viewed as attempted murder.

356
00:26:23,540 --> 00:26:25,250
Indict him for attempted murder.

357
00:26:25,250 --> 00:26:31,200
Even if he carried real bullets, if he intentionally used the blank ones, that cannot be attempted murder.

358
00:26:33,270 --> 00:26:36,180
We'll think more about that point.

359
00:26:36,180 --> 00:26:38,940
That isn't the focus of this case anyhow.

360
00:26:38,940 --> 00:26:42,600
Exactly. The focus is what his motive was.

361
00:26:42,600 --> 00:26:46,910
Why did he point a gun towards someone who saved the life of his brother?

362
00:26:54,280 --> 00:26:56,990
So you're saying that he's not a part of your revenge, right?

363
00:26:56,990 --> 00:26:59,530
I'll carry out my revenge with my own hands.

364
00:26:59,530 --> 00:27:03,100
Things have only gotten more complicated, thanks to Kim Han Yong.

365
00:27:05,810 --> 00:27:08,590
I would say so if I did it.

366
00:27:09,660 --> 00:27:14,040
They told you to go ahead since they're running late.

367
00:27:14,040 --> 00:27:15,790
Goodness, he's the same as ever.

368
00:27:15,790 --> 00:27:17,520
Is it someone you know?

369
00:27:17,520 --> 00:27:22,950
He was my senior at the law corps. He's probably late from playing golf.

370
00:27:22,950 --> 00:27:26,820
- Anyway, let's get him to talk.
- Yes, Sir.

371
00:27:26,820 --> 00:27:29,010
Have a seat.

372
00:27:30,110 --> 00:27:31,950
Kim Han Yong.

373
00:27:32,710 --> 00:27:36,260
Military Criminal Act Article 53. Plotting and murdering your superior.

374
00:27:36,260 --> 00:27:41,950
Though you have a right to remain silent, use it well. You're in a very serious situation.

375
00:27:45,560 --> 00:27:48,530
You shot at a battalion commander.

376
00:27:48,530 --> 00:27:53,690
Since the victim is your superior, your punishment will be even greater. Why did you shoot?

377
00:27:56,120 --> 00:28:00,040
On top of that, doing something like that to a benefactor who saved your brother's life?

378
00:28:00,040 --> 00:28:03,340
What a scumbag.

379
00:28:04,880 --> 00:28:07,010
Why? Did I touch a nerve?

380
00:28:07,010 --> 00:28:09,100
Which part? Saying scumbag?

381
00:28:09,100 --> 00:28:12,520
Or... benefactor?

382
00:28:13,910 --> 00:28:18,940
I'm just angry I wasn't able to blow that bastard's head off.

383
00:28:18,940 --> 00:28:20,580
Sure.

384
00:28:21,340 --> 00:28:23,560
You could've killed him.

385
00:28:23,560 --> 00:28:26,270
You had enough bullets, too.

386
00:28:26,270 --> 00:28:31,160
What? Were you afraid of the opportunity once you got it?

387
00:28:33,370 --> 00:28:37,860
See? He's a scumbag and a total wimp.

388
00:28:37,860 --> 00:28:40,980
You think I don't know your tricks?

389
00:28:40,980 --> 00:28:46,240
You're trying to get a reaction out of me and use my words to write up the story you want. Am I wrong?

390
00:28:46,240 --> 00:28:51,360
I will never trust military officers like you.

391
00:28:52,720 --> 00:28:56,940
You're also military personnel, and so is your hospitalized brother.

392
00:28:56,940 --> 00:29:01,140
Don't you dare speak of my poor brother!

393
00:29:01,140 --> 00:29:03,340
One thing's for certain.

394
00:29:03,340 --> 00:29:06,770
You shot for your brother.

395
00:29:06,770 --> 00:29:11,940
People think the Landmine Hero saved your brother but you disagree.

396
00:29:11,940 --> 00:29:16,140
But you have a reason you can't share with us.

397
00:29:16,140 --> 00:29:20,350
Not only do you not trust military personnel like us

398
00:29:20,350 --> 00:29:23,150
but also you loathe us.

399
00:29:28,060 --> 00:29:32,910
You found out some crucial information. The fact that he has something against the Landmine Hero.

400
00:29:32,910 --> 00:29:36,480
You take charge of this case. I'll support you in my own way .

401
00:29:36,480 --> 00:29:38,350
I understand.

402
00:29:39,810 --> 00:29:41,970
Already over?

403
00:29:41,970 --> 00:29:45,240
I came here for nothing. You still haven't left the military?

404
00:29:45,240 --> 00:29:49,200
No, things ended up that way.

405
00:29:49,200 --> 00:29:51,620
Oh, you're in charge of this case?

